CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 3 reads: " "Howdy, Senator" - Senator Kennedy received the warmest greeting accorded anyone since the days of F.D.R. and the 1936 campaign. Here he shakes hands with some admirers.  Constable Thomas J. Smith is second, left rear, facing camera.  Mrs. Mary Hodges, Fifth Ward chairlady is seen at the right."
TitMainTitle: Crowd surrounding John F. Kennedy, including police superintendent Slusser, Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith, and Mary Hodges wearing "Kennedy for President" sash, standing outside Gateway Center during Kennedy - Johnson campaign
